20out%20from%20anxious%20soon-to-be%20empty%20nesters%20in%20Facebook%20groups%20for%20parents%20of%20college%20students.%20They%20want%20to%20know%20as%20many%20details%20about%20the%20unknown%20as%20possible%2C%20down%20to%20whether%20their%20children%20need%20to%20bring%20their%20own%20toilet%20paper.%20Some%20questions%20are%20practical%20and%20logistical%3A%20where%20to%20find%20parking%20spots%20or%20places%20to%20eat%20when%20visiting%20for%20parents%20weekend.%20Others%20are%20so%20inane%20they%20offer%20a%20glimpse%20into%20a%20new%20era%20of%20helicopter%20parenting%2C%20when%20moms%20and%20dads%20micromanage%20every%20aspect%20of%20their%20children's%20lives%20into%20adulthood%2C%20from%20scheduling%20their%20medical%20appointments%20to%20arranging%20their%20bathing%20routines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gen%20Xers%20%E2%80%94%20who%20make%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20parents%20of%20today's%20teens%20and%20young%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20access%20to%20unlimited%20information%20about%20their%20kids%20started%20early.%20There%20are%20apps%20that%20allow%20parents%20to%20record%20the%20color%2C%20texture%2C%20and%20size%20of%20the%20contents%20of%20each%20soiled%20diaper.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-decline-in-kids-sports-new-model-cheaper-easier-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouth%20sports%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20extracurriculars%20have%20become%20so%20competitive%20that%20parents%20are%20tapping%20into%20group%20chats%20to%20learn%20the%20secrets%20to%20securing%20spots%20with%20the%20best%20coaches%20and%20instructors.%20They're%20looped%20into%20emails%20from%20schools%20with%20constant%20updates%20about%20their%20kids'%20grades.%20And%20as%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frejected-ivy-league-colleges-what-i-did-wrong-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einto%20top%20colleges%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20an%20American%20Ninja%20Warrior%20obstacle%20course%20of%20extracurriculars%2C%20parents%20have%20become%20round-the-clock%20managers%20and%20chauffeurs.%20Even%20once%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-age-kids-relationship-dynamics-changed-parenting-lessons-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekids%20are%20off%20to%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20parents%20don't%20want%20to%20let%20go%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-tracking-parents-location-sharing-phones-helicopter-parenting-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETracking%20family%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20location%20sharing%20has%20become%20a%20norm%20rather%20than%20an%20invasion%20of%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScrolling%20through%20some%20of%20these%20Facebook%20groups%20(there%20are%20thousands)%2C%20parents%20post%20dimensions%20or%20video%20tours%20of%20dorm%20rooms%20and%20beds%20and%20ask%20whether%20desks%20will%20come%20with%20or%20without%20shelves%20in%20certain%20rooms.%20TikTok%20abounds%20with%20screenshots%20from%20the%20worst%20offenders%2C%20including%20a%20parent%20asking%20how%20to%20contact%20professors%20to%20introduce%20themself%20before%20any%20issues%20arise%20with%20their%20kid%20in%20class%2C%20and%20another%20floating%20the%20idea%20of%20asking%20a%20college%20to%20install%20a%20camera%20in%20their%20child's%20dorm%20room%20to%20check%20whether%20they're%20sleeping%20enough.%20There%20are%20also%20reports%20of%20some%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2F2023%2F11%2Fhelicopter-parenting-college-kids.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eset%20up%20playdates%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20lonely%2018-year-olds%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20professors%20are%20taking%20to%20Reddit%20to%20anonymously%20share%20horror%20stories%20of%20parents%20intervening%20in%20their%20kids'%20coursework%2C%20by%20emailing%2C%20calling%2C%20or%20even%20showing%20up%20and%20peeking%20into%20classrooms%20to%20see%20whether%20their%20kids%20are%20at%20their%20desks.%20One%20exasperated%20professor%20wrote%20that%20a%20parent%20%26quot%3Bhelpfully%20advised%20me%20that%20my%20(college%20algebra)%20lecture%20was%20a%20little%20dry%20and%20maybe%20if%20I%20told%20more%20jokes%20her%20daughter%20would%20come%20to%20class.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20Gen%20X%20%E2%80%94%20the%20latchkey%20generation%20stereotyped%20for%20being%20laissez-faire%20and%20adrift%20%E2%80%94%20has%20evolved%20into%20stressed%2C%20overwhelmed%2C%20hypervigilant%20parents.%20Parenting%20is%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20pendulum%20where%20we%20tend%20to%20overcorrect%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Amelia%20Kelley%2C%20an%20author%20and%20therapist%20who's%20also%20a%20millennial%20parent%20of%20young%20kids.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20all%20these%20Gen%20X%20parents%20who%20were%20raised%20much%20more%20independently%20and%20free%20range%2C%20who%20are%20now%20being%20inundated%20with%20incredible%20amounts%20of%20information%20and%20technology%20and%20pressure%20for%20achievement%20with%20their%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20me%20thinks%20it's%20like%2C%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20involved%20parents%20and%20maybe%20there%20was%20something%20missing%2C%20and%20they're%20trying%20to%20fill%20those%20gaps%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Christine%2C%20a%20Gen%20X%20mom%20of%20three%20kids%20(two%20still%20in%20college%20and%20one%20graduate)%20who%20asked%20me%20not%20to%20use%20her%20last%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20adds%20that%20tech%2C%20especially%20the%20arsenal%20of%20surveillance%20tools%20at%20their%20disposal%2C%20has%20played%20a%20huge%20role%20in%20her%20generation's%20hyper-watchfulness.%20Many%20Gen%20Xers%20became%20parents%20just%20as%20Facebook%20groups%20and%20Listservs%20were%20born%2C%20and%20their%20arrival%20upended%20old%20parenting%20trends.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20so%20much%20access%20to%20everything%20that's%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Christine%20says.%20She%20regularly%20watches%20all%20three%20of%20her%20children's%20locations%20from%20her%20phone%2C%20just%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20make%20it%20home%20safely.%20(She%20swears%20she%20doesn't%20really%20care%20whether%20they're%20out%20partying.)%20Even%20though%20she%20can%20track%20their%20every%20move%2C%20Christine%20says%20she%20wants%20her%20kids%20to%20be%20independent%20and%20views%20college%20as%20a%20safely%20bubbled%20state%20of%20quasi-adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20quasi-adulthood%20is%20financial%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20is%20too%20expensive%20for%2018-year-olds%20to%20buy%20themselves.%20Whether%20it's%20lingering%20on%20the%20family%20phone%20or%20health%20insurance%20plan%20or%20getting%20help%20paying%20for%20rent%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Faverage-college-tuition%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520average%2520college%2520tuition%2520for%2Cincreased%25203.2%2525%2520year%2520over%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etuition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20meals%2C%20the%20financial%20web%20between%20parents%20and%20their%20children%20has%20grown%20more%20complex.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20graduates%20struggling%20to%20find%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20half-baked%20adulthood%20era%20can%20continue%20even%20longer%20as%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-home-after-graduating-college-saved-thousands-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20back%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20know%20our%20kids%20are%20coming%20home%20after%20college%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year%20or%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Tobey%20Grumet%20Segal%2C%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20who's%20the%20mother%20of%20a%20high%20schooler%20and%20a%20rising%20college%20sophomore.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20be%20part%20of%20their%20lives.%20They%20don't%20want%20us%20to%20completely%20step%20away%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20matter%20of%20deciding%20how%20much%20you%20want%20to%20put%20into%20it%20and%20when%20you%20feel%20it's%20best%20to%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20no%20clear%20stop%20sign.%20Thanks%20to%20Facebook%2C%20Reddit%2C%20and%20group%20chats%2C%20parents%20can%20gossip%20with%20one%20another%20about%20what's%20happening%20inside%20that%20college%20bubble.%20A%20support%20group%20for%20parents%20of%20New%20York%20University%20students%20boasts%20nearly%208%2C000%20members%20and%20averages%20several%20posts%20a%20day%3B%20one%20for%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%20has%20nearly%209%2C000%20parents.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20groomed%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20to%20be%20part%20of%20these%20groups%20way%20before%20the%20kids%20left%20for%20college%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Erin%20Mantz%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%20blog%20Gen%20X%20Girls%20Grow%20Up.%20The%20messages%20and%20group%20chats%20of%20parents%20started%20as%20early%20as%20preschool%2C%20she%20says%2C%20when%20she%20was%20organizing%20carpooling%20and%20sports%20with%20other%20parents.%20It's%20been%20a%20natural%20progression%20to%20join%20the%20Facebook%20parent%20groups%20at%20her%20two%20sons'%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20kids%2C%20Mantz%20says%2C%20want%20parents%20to%20be%20tapped%20in.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20necessarily%20want%20us%20to%20be%20sharing%20personal%20information%20or%20asking%20questions%20on%20their%20behalf%20to%20figure%20stuff%20out%20for%20them%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20want%20us%20to%20miss%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20scared%20to%20feel%20like%20we%20might%20be%20out%20of%20the%20loop.%26quot%3B%20But%20some%20of%20the%20questions%20lead%20her%20to%20wonder%20why%20parents%20are%20even%20posting.%20Mantz%20tells%20me%20she%20once%20saw%20a%20parent%20post%20that%20their%20kid%20had%20a%20headache%20for%20days%2C%20and%20they%20asked%20for%20advice%20on%20whether%20the%20kid%20should%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%20or%20take%20pain%20medicine.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20kind%20of%20scary%2C%20honestly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20past%20groups%20she%20had%20joined%20devolve%20is%20why%20Grumet%20Segal%20hasn't%20joined%20an%20online%20group%20for%20her%20college-age%20son.%20What%20started%20as%20groups%20to%20share%20hand-me-down%20baby%20items%20within%20the%20community%20evolved%20into%20nasty%20fighting%20and%20divisive%20parenting%20opinions%2C%20she%20says.%20All%20of%20this%20over-involved%20parenting%20makes%20her%20wonder%20whether%20the%20pendulum%20will%20swing%20back%20when%20Gen%20Zers%20become%20parents.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20wonder%20how%20we%20get%20out%20of%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20like%20a%20death%20spiral%20of%20helicoptering.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20groups%20serve%20as%20outlets%20for%20parents%20to%20commiserate%20or%20vent%20their%20ever-rising%20stress.%20Last%20year%2C%20US%20Surgeon%20General%20Vivek%20Murthy%20put%20out%20a%20public%20health%20advisory%20on%20the%20mental%20health%20and%20well-being%20of%20America's%20parents.%20%26quot%3BSomething%20has%20to%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20and%20fixing%20the%20issue%20%26quot%3Bwill%20also%20require%20us%20to%20rethink%20cultural%20norms%20around%20parenting.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%202023%20American%20Psychological%20Association%20survey%2C%20one-third%20of%20parents%20with%20children%20younger%20than%2018%20reported%20feeling%20high%20levels%20of%20stress%2C%20up%20from%2024%25%20of%20parents%20in%202019.%20Parents%20of%20children%20under%2018%20were%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20report%20feeling%20stressed%20about%20money%20and%20to%20say%20that%20most%20days%20they%20were%20so%20stressed%20that%20the%20pressure%20interfered%20with%20their%20ability%20to%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20all%20their%20worrying%20and%20attentiveness%2C%20parents%20aren't%20sparing%20Gen%20Z%20from%20stress.%20In%20the%20same%202023%20APA%20survey%2C%20people%2018%20to%2034%20reported%20being%20more%20stressed%20than%20other%20generations%20on%20average.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20amount%20of%20time%20young%20people%20spent%20socializing%20with%20friends%20in%20person%20dropped%20by%20about%2070%25%20between%202003%20and%202020%2C%20a%20study%20from%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Rochester%20found.%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20found%20in%202019%20that%20the%20time%20spent%20on%20homework%20had%20doubled%20compared%20with%20high%20schoolers%20in%20the%201990s.%20All%20of%20this%20comes%20as%20colleges%20have%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-rejected-generation-college-careers-jobs-dating-ghosting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20competitive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%202010s%2C%20college-bound%20high%20schoolers%20were%20applying%20to%20more%20universities%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20and%20admission%20rates%20at%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20nation's%20colleges%20dropped%20by%20at%20least%2010%25%20between%202002%20and%202017.%20For%20parents%2C%20the%20message%20has%20become%20that%20top%20students%2C%20athletes%2C%20and%20performers%20need%20full-time%20management%20to%20succeed%20in%20crowded%20pools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20balance%20to%20strike%20between%20parental%20involvement%20and%20suffocating%20kids%20with%20care.%20Dr.%20Gene%20Beresin%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20The%20Clay%20Center%20for%20Young%20Healthy%20Minds%20at%20Massachusetts%20General%20Hospital%2C%20says%20that%20while%20the%20government%20deems%20you%20an%20adult%20at%2018%2C%20adolescence%20lasts%20from%20about%2014%20all%20the%20way%20to%20age%2026%2C%20when%20the%20brain%20fully%20develops.%20Still%2C%20some%20parents%20overcompensate%20during%20these%20years%20and%20may%20rob%20their%20kids%20of%20the%20ability%20to%20cope%20with%20failure%20and%20adversity.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20trying%20to%20prevent%20unhappiness%2C%20and%20they're%20also%20trying%20to%20give%20the%20kids%20a%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Beresin%20says.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20really%20important%20to%20let%20our%20kids%20fall%20and%20let%20our%20kids%20fail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20said%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20parents%20who%20want%20the%20constant%20connection%20%E2%80%94%20many%20young%20adults%20continue%20to%20badger%20parents%20with%20Adulting%20101%20questions.%20Chip%20Leighton%2C%20a%20father%20of%20two%20who%20started%20posting%20his%20kids'%20zany%20questions%20to%20TikTok%20and%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BWhat%20Time%20is%20Noon%3F%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20phenomenon%2C%20says%20it's%20mostly%20positive%20that%20teen%20and%20young%20adult%20children%20and%20parents%20yearn%20to%20stay%20connected%2C%20especially%20when%20there%20are%20so%20many%20search%20and%20AI%20tools%20that%20provide%20instant%20answers.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20extreme%2C%20if%20the%20kids'%20first%20instinct%20is%20always%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20their%20parent%20for%20the%20answer%2C%20that's%20probably%20not%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%20Parents%20submit%20text%20messages%20from%20their%20kids%20to%20Leighton's%20TikTok%2C%20which%20takes%20lighthearted%20jabs%20at%20the%20pressing%20questions%20young%20people%20ask%20that%20seem%20dumb%20to%20those%20of%20us%20who%20have%20been%20filing%20our%20taxes%20for%20several%20years%2C%20such%20as%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20I%20put%20for%20make%20of%20car%3F%20Metal%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20I%20get%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20tax%20exempt%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20college%20students%20and%20recent%20grads%20still%20get%20a%20helping%20hand%20from%20mom%20and%20dad%2C%20that%20might%20ease%20the%20transition%20to%20real%20adulthood.%20But%20for%20parents%20who%20stay%20plugged%20in%2C%20there