ndian%20markets.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECawasji%20Patel%20funded%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20water%20tank%20to%20address%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20drinking%20water%20shortages%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20area%20being%20named%20after%20him.%20The%20tank%2C%20now%20defunct%2C%20is%20historically%20important%20as%20part%20of%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20early%20water%20infrastructure.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatel%E2%80%99s%20legacy%20is%20tied%20to%20public%20infrastructure%20philanthropy.%20The%20Gazetteer%20of%20Bombay%20City%20and%20Island%20(1909)%20notes%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20to%20the%20water%20project.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20as%20Bombay%20grew%2C%20a%20mango%20was%20named%20after%20him%E2%80%94a%20tribute%20from%20a%20city%20that%20remembered%20its%20patrons%20in%20sweet%2C%20lasting%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrown%20in%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20orchards%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20of%20Powai%20Lake%2C%20it%20later%20spread%20to%20orchards%20springing%20up%20in%20Thane%20and%20Pune.%20The%20Powai%20estate%20had%20one%20lakh%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidiya.net%2Fp%2Fkavasji-patel-framji-kavasji-banaji-mumbais-forgotten-heros%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20mango%20trees%20spread%20over%201334%20acres%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F402943%2Findia-mango-map-hidden-guide-season%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emango%20growing%20here%20was%20popular%20%3C%2Fa%3Eamong%20the%20British%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CBombay%20Mango%E2%80%9D.%20In%201833-34%2C%20it%20was%20more%20expensive%20than%20Ratnagiri%E2%80%99s%20mango.%20On%20May%2018%2C%201838%2C%20a%20basket%20of%20this%20famous%20Bombay%20Mango%20was%20sent%20to%20Queen%20Victoria%20of%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGreen%20fruit%20with%20white%20pulp%3A%20What%20made%20this%20mago%20unique%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fruit%20was%20typically%20harvested%20green%20with%20white%20pulp%2C%20making%20it%20unique%20among%20mangoes.%20It%20was%20fibreless%2C%20which%20made%20it%20an%20excellent%20choice%20for%20cooking%2C%20especially%20for%20making%20jams%20and%20jellies%E2%80%94a%20quality%20appreciated%20by%20both%20Europeans%20and%20the%20Parsee%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20in%20Vechale%2C%20Cawasji%20Patel%20lives%20again%E2%80%94not%20in%20stone%20or%20brass%2C%20but%20in%20the%20flesh%20of%20a%20mango%2C%20sweet%20with%20memory%20and%20dripping%20with%20reverence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FA-Close-up-view-of-mango-tree-at-Deshmukh-familys-farm_11zon-1753443530-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476158%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThis%20mango%20tree%2C%20growing%20quietly%20in%20a%20rural%20farm%2C%20connects%20to%20the%20busy%20Cawasji%20Patel%20Street%20in%20Fort%20and%20the%20old%20CP%20Tank.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20variety%20is%20considered%20obscure%20and%20rare%20in%20Indian%20markets%20as%20it%20is%20overshadowed%20by%20commercially%20successful%20varieties%20like%20the%20Alphonso%2C%20Kesar%2C%20Dasehri%2C%20and%20their%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cawasji%20(or%20Kawasji)%20Patel%20mango%20quietly%20faded%20from%20view%E2%80%94and%20from%20collective%20memory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20ago%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fpune-news%2Ftaste-of-life-sharing-food-spreading-faith-and-fellowship-101735154017584.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Chinmay%20Damle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20and%20food%20enthusiast%2C%20noted%20that%20specimens%20from%20Pune%E2%80%99s%20Ganeshkhind%20Botanical%20Gardens%20had%20once%20been%20dispatched%20abroad%20and%20stood%20tall%20in%20various%20farms%20and%20gardens%20across%20Europe%20and%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20overlooked%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20variety%20still%20exists%20in%20some%20Indian%20orchards%2C%20he%20did%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20failed%20efforts%20to%20export%20it%20during%20an%20era%20predating%20refrigeration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E57-year-old%20Deshmukh%20is%20the%20only%20custodian%20of%20this%20forgotten%20variety.%20%E2%80%9C12%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20was%20gifted%20a%20scion%20of%20Cowasji%20Patil%2C%20which%20I%20grafted%20on%20a%20%3Cem%3Eraiwal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(indigenous)%20mango%20tree.%20This%20June%2C%20I%20got%2050%20pieces%20of%20this%20variety%2C%20each%20mango%20weighed%201003%20grams.%20But%20people%20rarely%20buy%20it%20as%20it%E2%80%99s%20unlike%20Hapus%20or%20Kesar%2C%20not%20sweet%20enough%20for%20our%20palate.%20But%20perfect%20for%20diabetics%2C%E2%80%9D%20Deshmukh%20says.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECawasji%20Patel%3A%20one%20of%20the%20few%20mangoes%20named%20after%20people%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20out%20of%20the%201%2C500%20mango%20varieties%20found%20in%20India%2C%20only%20a%20few%20are%20named%20after%20people.%20Cawasji%20Patel%20shares%20this%20rare%20honour%20with%20a%20select%20few.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20602px)%20100vw%2C%20602px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-weighing-1031-grams_11zon-1753443564.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-weighing-1031-grams_11zon-1753443564.jpg%20602w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-weighing-1031-grams_11zon-1753443564-300x271.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-weighing-1031-grams_11zon-1753443564-500x452.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-weighing-1031-grams_11zon-1753443564-150x136.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476164%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22544%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOnce%20a%20household%20name%20in%20Gujarati%20homes%2C%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20was%20cherished%20for%20its%20large%20size%2C%20small%20seed%2C%20and%20sweet%20pulp%2C%20especially%20for%20making%20%3Cem%3Epickles%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emurabba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Echhundo%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20Amrapali%2C%20named%20after%20the%20legendary%20dancer%20and%20courtesan%20from%20ancient%20Vaishali%3B%20Alphonso%2C%20which%20pays%20tribute%20to%20a%20Portuguese%20general%20from%20the%2018th%20century%3B%20and%20Kesar%2C%20once%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3ESalebhai%E2%80%99s%20Ambdi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20renamed%20by%20Nawab%20Mahabat%20Khan%20III%20in%201934.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20well-known%20variety%20is%20Chausa%E2%80%94not%20named%20after%20a%20person%2C%20but%20after%20a%20place%20and%20a%20historic%20event.%20In%201539%2C%20after%20defeating%20the%20Mughal%20emperor%20Humayun%20in%20Chausa%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Sher%20Shah%20Suri%20renamed%20his%20favourite%20mango%E2%80%94originally%20called%20%3Cem%3EGhazipuria%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94as%20%3Cem%3EChausa%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20orchards%20to%20archives%3A%20The%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20in%20global%20research%20collections%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fbook%2F10.1007%2F978-3-030-47829-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpringer%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Mango%20Genome%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20does%20mention%20the%20Cawasji%20(Cowasji)%20Patel%20mango%20variety%20and%20includes%20an%20image%20of%20the%20fruit%2C%20too.%20The%20book%20specifically%20notes%20that%20%E2%80%9Chybrids%20were%20developed%20from%20the%20cross%20Cowasji%20Patel%20%C3%97%20Pairi%2C%20with%20three%20hybrids%20isolated%20from%20153%20crosses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Agricultural%20Research%20Service%20(ARS)%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%E2%80%99s%20(USDA)%20National%20Germplasm%20Repository%20in%20Miami%2C%20Florida%2C%20includes%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20in%20its%20collection%20of%20over%20300%20mango%20types.%20While%20listing%20well-known%20varieties%20from%20Western%20India%20like%20Alphonso%2C%20Pairi%2C%20and%20Fernandin%2C%20author%20Sanjana%20Venu%20also%20highlights%20Cawasji%20Patel%20as%20an%20important%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20is%20no%20longer%20found%20in%20most%20orchards%20across%20Maharashtra%20and%20Gujarat%2C%20it%20is%20still%20preserved%20as%20germplasm%20in%20several%20important%20research%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20the%20Fruit%20Research%20Station%20(FRS)%20in%20Vengurla%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Agricultural%20Sciences%20in%20Dharwad%20(which%20houses%2067%20other%20mango%20varieties)%2C%20Mahatma%20Phule%20Krishi%20Vidyapeeth%20in%20Ahilyanagar%2C%20and%20the%20Laldhori%20Botanical%20Garden%20near%20the%20Girnar%20mountains%2C%20managed%20by%20Junagadh%20Agricultural%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELaldhori%E2%80%99s%20living%20library%20of%20mango%20diversity%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Cawasji%20mango%20tree%20at%20Laldhori%20is%20around%2080%20years%20old%E2%80%94a%20rare%20and%20regionally%20significant%20variety%20cultivated%20primarily%20for%20conservation%20and%20genetic%20diversity%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Dr%20Dharmendra%20Mehta%2C%20Professor%20and%20Head%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Genetics%20and%20Plant%20Breeding%20at%20Junagadh%20Agricultural%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocated%20in%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Bhavnath%20foothills%2C%20the%20Laldhori%20Botanical%20Garden%20is%20home%20to%20over%201%2C000%20species%E2%80%94from%20sandalwood%20and%20teak%20to%20aromatic%20herbs%20like%20clove%2C%20cardamom%2C%20and%20cinnamon.%20Among%20these%2C%20the%20garden%20also%20holds%20a%20germplasm%20collection%20featuring%20dozens%20of%20lesser-known%20mango%20varieties%2C%20including%20the%20elusive%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-tree-at-Laldhori-Botanica-Gardens_11zon-1753443551-500x664.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-tree-at-Laldhori-Botanica-Gardens_11zon-1753443551-500x664.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-tree-at-Laldhori-Botanica-Gardens_11zon-1753443551-226x300.jpg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-tree-at-Laldhori-Botanica-Gardens_11zon-1753443551-150x199.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCawasji-Patel-Mango-tree-at-Laldhori-Botanica-Gardens_11zon-1753443551.jpg%20614w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476162%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThough%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20is%20no%20longer%20found%20in%20most%20orchards%20across%20Maharashtra%20and%20Gujarat%2C%20it%20is%20still%20preserved%20as%20germplasm%20in%20several%20important%20research%20centres.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20mangoes%20aren%E2%80%99t%20widely%20commercialised%20or%20sold%20in%20markets%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Dr%20Dharmendra.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20they%20hold%20tremendous%20value%20for%20research%2C%20genetic%20conservation%2C%20and%20preserving%20our%20horticultural%20heritage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20June%2C%20Junagadh%20Agricultural%20University%20hosts%20its%20Mango%20Festival%2C%20a%20celebration%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20mango%20biodiversity.%20It%20was%20at%20one%20such%20festival%20that%20Sumeet%20Samsudin%20Jhariya%2C%20an%20Indian%20Agricultural%20Research%20Institute%20(IARI)%20Innovative%20Farmer%20awardee%20from%20Junagadh%E2%80%99s%20Bhalchel%20village%2C%20first%20came%20across%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20variety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20it%20among%20more%20than%20150%20varieties%20displayed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20over%20200%20mango%20varieties%20growing%20on%20my%20farm%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20a%20sapling%E2%80%94but%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20one.%20I%20still%20keep%20a%20photo%20of%20it%20saved%20on%20my%20phone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20variety%20that%20rules%20Gujarati%20kitchens%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F255025%2Fhow-to-grow-mango-tree-girdling-harvest-fruits-alphonso-kesar-rajesh-shah-gujarat-farmer-senile-narendra-modi-sustainable%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousehold%20name%20in%20Gujarati%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20mango%20was%20cherished%20for%20its%20large%20size%2C%20small%20seed%2C%20and%20sweet%20pulp%2C%20especially%20for%20making%20%3Cem%3Epickles%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emurabba%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Echhundo%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20as%20high-yielding%20commercial%20varieties%20like%20Totapuri%20and%20Rajapuri%20gained%20dominance%2C%20farmers%20moved%20away%20from%20cultivating%20this%20heritage%20mango%E2%80%94leading%20to%20its%20quiet%20disappearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20know%20they%E2%80%99ve%20lost%20something%20special%2C%E2%80%9D%20reflects%20Dr%20Dharmendra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20or%20not%20the%20Cawasji%20Patel%20is%20truly%20unmatched%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20debate%E2%80%94but%20its%20conservation%2C%20and%20that%20of%20other%20forgotten%20varieties%2C%20is%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPreserving%20the%20germplasm%E2%80%94the%20genetic%20material%E2%80%94of%20traditional%20mango%20varieties%20is%20key%20to%20biodiversity%2C%20sustainable%20agriculture%2C%20and%20food%20security%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Anant%20Morade%2C%20fruit%20scientist%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fniam.